---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";

const year = new Date().getFullYear();
---

<Layout>
	<a
		href="#main"
		class="sr-only focus:not-sr-only focus:fixed focus:left-4 focus:top-4 focus:z-50 rounded-xl border border-slate-200 bg-white/90 px-3 py-2 text-sm font-semibold text-slate-900 shadow-lg backdrop-blur"
	>
		Skip to content
	</a>

	<header class="sticky top-0 z-40 border-b border-slate-200/70 bg-white/70 backdrop-blur">
		<div class="mx-auto flex w-full max-w-6xl items-center justify-between px-5 py-3">
			<a href="/" class="group flex items-center gap-2.5 font-extrabold tracking-tight text-slate-900">
				<span
					aria-hidden="true"
						class="h-4 w-4 rounded-md bg-linear-to-br from-fuchsia-500 via-violet-500 to-cyan-400 shadow-sm ring-1 ring-black/5"
				></span>
				<span class="text-sm sm:text-base">Ready Set Gem</span>
			</a>

			<nav class="hidden items-center gap-1 sm:flex" aria-label="Primary">
				<a class="rounded-xl px-3 py-2 text-sm font-semibold text-slate-700 hover:bg-slate-100" href="#process">Process</a>
				<a class="rounded-xl px-3 py-2 text-sm font-semibold text-slate-700 hover:bg-slate-100" href="#pricing">Pricing</a>
				<a class="rounded-xl px-3 py-2 text-sm font-semibold text-slate-700 hover:bg-slate-100" href="#faq">FAQ</a>
				<a
					class="ml-1 rounded-xl bg-slate-900 px-3 py-2 text-sm font-semibold text-white shadow-sm hover:bg-slate-800"
					href="#contact"
				>
					Start
				</a>
			</nav>

			<a
				class="sm:hidden rounded-xl bg-slate-900 px-3 py-2 text-sm font-semibold text-white shadow-sm hover:bg-slate-800"
				href="#contact"
			>
				Start
			</a>
		</div>
	</header>

	<main id="main">
		<section class="relative overflow-hidden">
			<div class="absolute inset-0 -z-10">
				<div class="absolute -top-24 left-1/2 h-[540px] w-[900px] -translate-x-1/2 rounded-full bg-linear-to-r from-fuchsia-300/35 via-violet-300/30 to-cyan-300/35 blur-3xl"></div>
				<div class="absolute -bottom-40 left-1/2 h-[520px] w-[860px] -translate-x-1/2 rounded-full bg-linear-to-r from-amber-200/25 via-rose-200/20 to-sky-200/25 blur-3xl"></div>
			</div>

			<div class="mx-auto w-full max-w-6xl px-5 pb-10 pt-12 sm:pt-16">
				<p class="text-sm font-semibold tracking-wide text-slate-600">
					Kingston, Ontario • Proudly Canadian
				</p>
				<h1 class="mt-3 text-4xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-slate-950 sm:text-5xl">
					Trading card restoration for collectors.
				</h1>
				<p class="mt-4 max-w-3xl text-lg leading-relaxed text-slate-700 sm:text-xl">
					We restore Pokémon, Yu‑Gi‑Oh!, Magic: The Gathering, and more through careful inspection, a clear restoration plan,
					and conservative, collector‑first work—so your cards can be display‑worthy again.
				</p>

				<div class="mt-6 flex flex-wrap items-center gap-3">
					<a
						class="inline-flex items-center justify-center rounded-2xl bg-linear-to-r from-fuchsia-600 via-violet-600 to-cyan-500 px-5 py-3 text-sm font-extrabold text-white shadow-lg shadow-violet-500/15 ring-1 ring-black/5 hover:opacity-95"
						href="#contact"
					>
						Request a review
					</a>
					<a
						class="inline-flex items-center justify-center rounded-2xl bg-white/70 px-5 py-3 text-sm font-extrabold text-slate-800 ring-1 ring-slate-200 shadow-sm hover:bg-white"
						href="#process"
					>
						See the process
					</a>
				</div>

				<div class="mt-7 flex flex-wrap gap-2" role="list" aria-label="Key details">
					<div class="rounded-full bg-white/75 px-4 py-2 text-sm font-semibold text-slate-700 ring-1 ring-slate-200" role="listitem">
						<strong class="font-extrabold text-slate-900">$50 / card</strong> (minimum 5)
					</div>
					<div class="rounded-full bg-white/75 px-4 py-2 text-sm font-semibold text-slate-700 ring-1 ring-slate-200" role="listitem">
						<strong class="font-extrabold text-slate-900">3–14 days</strong> typical turnaround
					</div>
					<div class="rounded-full bg-white/75 px-4 py-2 text-sm font-semibold text-slate-700 ring-1 ring-slate-200" role="listitem">
						<strong class="font-extrabold text-slate-900">UV/blacklight</strong> + magnification inspection
					</div>
				</div>

				<p class="mt-5 max-w-3xl text-sm text-slate-600">
					Restoration isn’t the same as “grading prep.” If we see a grading concern, we’ll flag it before we proceed.
				</p>
			</div>
		</section>

		<section class="py-10">
			<div class="mx-auto w-full max-w-6xl px-5">
				<div class="grid gap-4 md:grid-cols-3">
					<div class="rounded-3xl bg-white/70 p-6 ring-1 ring-slate-200 shadow-sm">
						<h2 class="text-base font-extrabold tracking-tight text-slate-950">Inspection, done properly</h2>
						<p class="mt-2 text-slate-700">
							Magnification + <strong class="font-extrabold text-slate-900">UV/blacklight inspection</strong> to spot inconsistencies,
							previous work, or surface concerns before we touch the card.
						</p>
					</div>
					<div class="rounded-3xl bg-white/70 p-6 ring-1 ring-slate-200 shadow-sm">
						<h2 class="text-base font-extrabold tracking-tight text-slate-950">A plan you approve</h2>
						<p class="mt-2 text-slate-700">
							We explain risks, expected outcomes, and what steps we recommend—then you confirm before restoration begins.
						</p>
					</div>
					<div class="rounded-3xl bg-white/70 p-6 ring-1 ring-slate-200 shadow-sm">
						<h2 class="text-base font-extrabold tracking-tight text-slate-950">Documented results</h2>
						<p class="mt-2 text-slate-700">
							Consistent intake/final photos and careful packaging for return shipping or pickup in the Kingston area.
						</p>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>
		</section>

		<section class="py-12" id="services">
			<div class="mx-auto w-full max-w-6xl px-5">
				<div class="max-w-3xl">
					<h2 class="text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-slate-950">What we restore</h2>
					<p class="mt-2 text-slate-700">
						We focus on stabilizing and improving presentation while respecting the card’s integrity. If a card is too damaged,
						we’ll tell you up front.
					</p>
				</div>

				<div class="mt-6 grid gap-4 lg:grid-cols-3">
					<div class="rounded-3xl bg-white p-6 ring-1 ring-slate-200 shadow-sm">
						<h3 class="text-base font-extrabold text-slate-950">Supported games</h3>
						<ul class="mt-3 list-disc space-y-2 pl-5 text-slate-700">
							<li>Pokémon</li>
							<li>Yu‑Gi‑Oh!</li>
							<li>Magic: The Gathering</li>
							<li>Sports & other TCG/CCGs</li>
						</ul>
					</div>
					<div class="rounded-3xl bg-white p-6 ring-1 ring-slate-200 shadow-sm">
						<h3 class="text-base font-extrabold text-slate-950">Common issues we can address</h3>
						<ul class="mt-3 list-disc space-y-2 pl-5 text-slate-700">
							<li>Surface grime / handling residue (controlled cleaning)</li>
							<li>Careful surface polish when appropriate</li>
							<li>Light warping / bends (stabilization where safe)</li>
							<li>Minor adhesive residue (case-by-case)</li>
							<li>Edge roughness and lift risks (stabilization)</li>
							<li>Pressure marks/dents (assessment required)</li>
						</ul>
					</div>
					<div class="rounded-3xl bg-linear-to-br from-amber-50 via-white to-rose-50 p-6 ring-1 ring-amber-200/60 shadow-sm">
						<h3 class="text-base font-extrabold text-slate-950">What we don’t do</h3>
						<ul class="mt-3 list-disc space-y-2 pl-5 text-slate-700">
							<li>Trimming, sanding, or re-shaping corners</li>
							<li>Recoloring, ink touch-ups, or print simulation</li>
							<li>Any hidden work meant to fool graders</li>
						</ul>
						<p class="mt-3 text-sm text-slate-600">
							Surface polishing: when appropriate, we may perform careful, controlled polishing to improve presentation (e.g., reducing
							visible handling haze/scuffs). Results vary by card finish and damage, and we keep the approach conservative and
							collector-first.
						</p>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>
		</section>

		<section class="py-12" id="process">
			<div class="mx-auto w-full max-w-6xl px-5">
				<div class="max-w-3xl">
					<h2 class="text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-slate-950">Our restoration process</h2>
					<p class="mt-2 text-slate-700">
						Careful, documented, and approval-based. Typical turnaround is <strong class="font-extrabold text-slate-900">3–14 days</strong>
						depending on damage, drying/settling time, and workload.
					</p>
				</div>

				<ol class="mt-6 grid gap-4 md:grid-cols-2" aria-label="Ready Set Gem restoration workflow">
					<li class="rounded-3xl bg-white p-6 ring-1 ring-slate-200 shadow-sm">
						<div class="text-sm font-extrabold text-slate-950">1) Intake + photos</div>
						<p class="mt-2 text-slate-700">We log each card, photograph it under consistent lighting, and note obvious concerns.</p>
					</li>
					<li class="rounded-3xl bg-white p-6 ring-1 ring-slate-200 shadow-sm">
						<div class="text-sm font-extrabold text-slate-950">2) Close inspection</div>
						<p class="mt-2 text-slate-700">Magnified review of surface, edges, corners, and stock behavior (warp, bend memory).</p>
					</li>
					<li class="rounded-3xl bg-white p-6 ring-1 ring-slate-200 shadow-sm">
						<div class="text-sm font-extrabold text-slate-950">3) UV/blacklight inspection</div>
						<p class="mt-2 text-slate-700">
							We check fluorescence and inconsistencies that can indicate prior alteration, contamination, or uneven materials—then
							factor that into the plan.
						</p>
					</li>
					<li class="rounded-3xl bg-white p-6 ring-1 ring-slate-200 shadow-sm">
						<div class="text-sm font-extrabold text-slate-950">4) Condition report + plan</div>
						<p class="mt-2 text-slate-700">
							You get a summary of risks, expected results, and what we recommend. Work starts only after you approve.
						</p>
					</li>
					<li class="rounded-3xl bg-white p-6 ring-1 ring-slate-200 shadow-sm">
						<div class="text-sm font-extrabold text-slate-950">5) Restoration work</div>
						<p class="mt-2 text-slate-700">
							Controlled cleaning and stabilization steps chosen for the specific card/finish. We avoid aggressive methods that
							increase alteration risk.
						</p>
					</li>
					<li class="rounded-3xl bg-white p-6 ring-1 ring-slate-200 shadow-sm">
						<div class="text-sm font-extrabold text-slate-950">6) Final photos + return</div>
						<p class="mt-2 text-slate-700">
							We photograph results, package securely, and arrange return shipping or local pickup (Kingston area).
						</p>
					</li>
				</ol>
			</div>
		</section>

		<section class="py-12" id="pricing">
			<div class="mx-auto w-full max-w-6xl px-5">
				<div class="max-w-3xl">
					<h2 class="text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-slate-950">Pricing</h2>
					<p class="mt-2 text-slate-700">Straightforward, per-card pricing with a minimum order size so we can do the process properly.</p>
				</div>

				<div class="mt-6 grid gap-4 lg:grid-cols-2">
					<div class="rounded-3xl bg-linear-to-br from-fuchsia-50 via-white to-cyan-50 p-6 ring-1 ring-slate-200 shadow-sm">
						<div class="flex items-start justify-between gap-4">
							<div>
								<div class="text-5xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-slate-950">$50</div>
								<div class="mt-1 text-sm font-semibold text-slate-700">per card</div>
							</div>
							<div class="rounded-2xl bg-white/80 px-3 py-2 text-sm font-extrabold text-slate-900 ring-1 ring-slate-200">
								Minimum 5 cards/order
							</div>
						</div>
						<ul class="mt-5 list-disc space-y-2 pl-5 text-slate-700">
							<li>Inspection + condition report</li>
							<li>UV/blacklight check for inconsistencies</li>
							<li>Plan approval before work begins</li>
							<li>Restoration work (case-by-case)</li>
							<li>Before/after photos</li>
						</ul>
						<p class="mt-3 text-sm text-slate-600">
							Shipping isn’t included. Inbound shipping is typically paid by the collector; return shipping is billed at cost with tracking
							(optional insurance available). Local drop-off may be available by appointment.
						</p>
					</div>

					<div class="rounded-3xl bg-white p-6 ring-1 ring-slate-200 shadow-sm">
						<h3 class="text-base font-extrabold text-slate-950">Important note about grading</h3>
						<p class="mt-2 text-slate-700">
							Some cards are so damaged that meaningful improvement would be considered <strong class="font-extrabold text-slate-900">alteration</strong>
							under major grading standards (PSA/BGS/CGC). If we believe a card is likely to be rejected—or if the work would push it into
							alteration territory—we will recommend against restoration for grading purposes.
						</p>
						<p class="mt-3 text-sm text-slate-600">
							This service is best for collectors who want to preserve and display cherished cards that suffered damage. We do not promise grade outcomes.
						</p>

						<div class="my-5 h-px w-full bg-slate-200"></div>

						<h3 class="text-base font-extrabold text-slate-950">How to send cards safely</h3>
						<ul class="mt-3 list-disc space-y-2 pl-5 text-slate-700">
							<li>Penny sleeve + semi-rigid holder (Card Saver) or toploader</li>
							<li>Team bag (or painter’s tape on toploader—no adhesive on the card)</li>
							<li>Bubble wrap + sturdy box (avoid envelopes for higher value orders)</li>
							<li>Include a list of cards + your contact info</li>
						</ul>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>
		</section>

		<section class="py-12" id="faq">
			<div class="mx-auto w-full max-w-6xl px-5">
				<div class="max-w-3xl">
					<h2 class="text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-slate-950">FAQ</h2>
					<p class="mt-2 text-slate-700">Honest answers for collectors.</p>
				</div>

				<div class="mt-6 grid gap-4 lg:grid-cols-2">
					<details class="group rounded-3xl bg-white p-6 ring-1 ring-slate-200 shadow-sm" open>
						<summary class="cursor-pointer list-none text-base font-extrabold text-slate-950">
							Will restoration increase my grade?
						</summary>
						<p class="mt-3 text-slate-700">
							Not guaranteed. Grading companies may flag certain improvements as alteration, and some defects (ink loss, creases, stock separation)
							may remain visible. Our goal is careful, collector-first restoration for presentation—never “tricks.”
						</p>
					</details>
					<details class="group rounded-3xl bg-white p-6 ring-1 ring-slate-200 shadow-sm">
						<summary class="cursor-pointer list-none text-base font-extrabold text-slate-950">
							Why is there a 5-card minimum?
						</summary>
						<p class="mt-3 text-slate-700">
							Proper restoration requires controlled inspection, documentation, and time between steps. A minimum of <strong class="font-extrabold text-slate-900">5 cards per order</strong>
							keeps the workflow efficient while maintaining the level of care each card deserves.
						</p>
					</details>
					<details class="group rounded-3xl bg-white p-6 ring-1 ring-slate-200 shadow-sm">
						<summary class="cursor-pointer list-none text-base font-extrabold text-slate-950">
							What kinds of cards do you reject?
						</summary>
						<p class="mt-3 text-slate-700">
							Cards with severe stock separation, heavy water damage/mold risk, significant ink loss, or cases where any meaningful improvement would likely be considered alteration.
							We’d rather decline than risk harming a treasured card.
						</p>
					</details>
					<details class="group rounded-3xl bg-white p-6 ring-1 ring-slate-200 shadow-sm">
						<summary class="cursor-pointer list-none text-base font-extrabold text-slate-950">
							What does UV/blacklight inspection do?
						</summary>
						<p class="mt-3 text-slate-700">
							Under UV/blacklight, some materials fluoresce differently. It can reveal inconsistencies that suggest prior alteration, contamination, or unusual spots—useful for deciding what’s safe before we touch the card.
						</p>
					</details>
					<details class="group rounded-3xl bg-white p-6 ring-1 ring-slate-200 shadow-sm">
						<summary class="cursor-pointer list-none text-base font-extrabold text-slate-950">
							How long does it take?
						</summary>
						<p class="mt-3 text-slate-700">
							Typical turnaround is <strong class="font-extrabold text-slate-900">3–14 days</strong>, depending on the number of cards, damage complexity, and any necessary settling time between steps.
						</p>
					</details>
					<details class="group rounded-3xl bg-white p-6 ring-1 ring-slate-200 shadow-sm">
						<summary class="cursor-pointer list-none text-base font-extrabold text-slate-950">
							How do you handle shipping and risk?
						</summary>
						<p class="mt-3 text-slate-700">
							We recommend tracked shipping and protective packaging. Return shipping is billed at cost and can include insurance. Restoration always carries some risk; we document condition at intake and get plan approval before starting any work.
						</p>
					</details>
				</div>
			</div>
		</section>

		<section class="py-12" id="contact">
			<div class="mx-auto w-full max-w-6xl px-5">
				<div class="rounded-[28px] bg-linear-to-br from-slate-900 via-slate-900 to-slate-800 p-1 shadow-lg shadow-slate-900/10">
					<div class="rounded-[26px] bg-linear-to-br from-white/10 via-white/5 to-white/10 p-7 ring-1 ring-white/10">
						<div class="grid gap-6 lg:grid-cols-[1.2fr_.8fr]">
							<div>
								<h2 class="text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-white">Start with a review</h2>
								<p class="mt-2 text-white/80">
									Send a few photos and a short description. We’ll reply with a recommended plan, risks to consider, and next steps.
								</p>
								<ul class="mt-4 list-disc space-y-2 pl-5 text-white/85">
									<li><strong class="font-extrabold text-white">Location:</strong> Kingston, Ontario, Canada</li>
									<li><strong class="font-extrabold text-white">Pricing:</strong> $50/card (minimum 5)</li>
									<li><strong class="font-extrabold text-white">Turnaround:</strong> typically 3–14 days</li>
								</ul>
							</div>
							<div class="flex flex-col items-start gap-3">
								<a
									class="inline-flex w-full items-center justify-center rounded-2xl bg-linear-to-r from-fuchsia-500 via-violet-500 to-cyan-400 px-5 py-3 text-sm font-extrabold text-slate-950 shadow-lg shadow-fuchsia-500/20 ring-1 ring-white/10 hover:opacity-95"
									href="mailto:hello@readysetgem.ca?subject=Ready%20Set%20Gem%20—%20Restoration%20Request&body=Hi%20Ready%20Set%20Gem%2C%0A%0AHere%E2%80%99s%20what%20I%E2%80%99d%20like%20restored%3A%0A-%20Game%20(Pok%C3%A9mon%2FYu-Gi-Oh!%2FMTG%2Fother)%3A%0A-%20#%20of%20cards%3A%0A-%20Damage%20summary%3A%0A-%20Goal%20(display%2Fcollection%2Fgrading)%3A%0A-%20Photos%20link%3A%0A%0AThanks!"
								>
									Email for a review
								</a>
								<a
									class="inline-flex w-full items-center justify-center rounded-2xl bg-white/10 px-5 py-3 text-sm font-extrabold text-white ring-1 ring-white/15 hover:bg-white/15"
									href="#pricing"
								>
									Review pricing
								</a>
								<p class="text-sm text-white/65">Replace the email address in code if needed.</p>
							</div>
						</div>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>
		</section>
	</main>

	<footer class="border-t border-slate-200/70 bg-white/60 py-10">
		<div class="mx-auto flex w-full max-w-6xl flex-col justify-between gap-6 px-5 md:flex-row">
			<div>
				<div class="flex items-center gap-2.5 font-extrabold tracking-tight text-slate-900">
					<span
						aria-hidden="true"
						class="h-4 w-4 rounded-md bg-linear-to-br from-fuchsia-500 via-violet-500 to-cyan-400 ring-1 ring-black/5"
					></span>
					<span>Ready Set Gem</span>
				</div>
				<p class="mt-2 text-slate-600">Trading card restoration in Kingston, Ontario — proudly Canadian.</p>
				<p class="mt-4 text-sm text-slate-500">© {year} Ready Set Gem. All rights reserved.</p>
			</div>
			<div class="flex flex-wrap items-center gap-2">
				<a class="rounded-xl px-3 py-2 text-sm font-semibold text-slate-700 hover:bg-slate-100" href="#process">Process</a>
				<a class="rounded-xl px-3 py-2 text-sm font-semibold text-slate-700 hover:bg-slate-100" href="#pricing">Pricing</a>
				<a class="rounded-xl px-3 py-2 text-sm font-semibold text-slate-700 hover:bg-slate-100" href="#faq">FAQ</a>
				<a class="rounded-xl px-3 py-2 text-sm font-semibold text-slate-700 hover:bg-slate-100" href="#contact">Contact</a>
			</div>
		</div>
	</footer>
</Layout>
